  "doc_id": "30551",
  "text": "The remaining forty-two E. coli isolates with AmpC-resistance phenotype and without either an ESBL or pAmpC were further investigated. Sequencing of the promoter region of the chromosomal ampC revealed different mutations that have been linked to resistance to third-generation cephalosporins in 29 isolates [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . These mutations were found at the positions -1, -18,-42, -82, -88, and +58, and an insertion of an amino acid between the -10 and -35 region of the promoter. No mechanism was elucidated for the remaining 13 isolates.",
